bug.short_desc: generator fails to build a demo application when pulling in a skeleton app (widgetbrowser)

long_desc.thetext:
Created attachment 1371 redirected output of generate -w source (qx-v2.1)
if you follow this article (Three steps for efficient theme development, look below for the URL) using a qx-v4.1 sdk, you'll end up with this error message:
$ ./generate.py
---------------------------------------------------------------------------- Initializing: default ---------------------------------------------------------------------------- >>> Processing configuration >>> Warning: ! Skipping unknown 'export' job: "simulation-build" >>> Warning: ! Skipping unknown 'export' job: "simulation-run" >>> Warning: ! Skipping unknown 'export' job: "test" >>> Warning: ! Skipping unknown 'export' job: "test-source"
---------------------------------------------------------------------------- Executing: source-hybrid::source-script ---------------------------------------------------------------------------- - Populating the cache, this may take some time >>> Scanning libraries - Including part classes... <type 'exceptions.RuntimeError'> : Expression gives no results. Malformed entry: include
using a qx-v2.1 sdk (just change QOOXDOO_PATH to the older sdk) fixes this problem.
1) http://manual.qooxdoo.org/2.1/pages/desktop/ui_using_widgetbrowser_for_theme_development.html

Created attachment 1372 redirected output of generate -w source (qx-v4.1)
if you compare both outputs, look for the "u'library':" and "u'packages'" parts.
